<div>
  <p>Hey <%= @seller.name_or_username %>,</p>
  <p>
    We've noticed a high rate of chargebacks on your account. When customers can't get a refund,
    they often go to their bank instead — and every chargeback costs you the sale plus a dispute fee,
    and puts your account at risk with payment processors.
  </p>
  <p>
    To help bring your dispute rate down, we've updated your account's refund policy to
    <strong><%= @seller.refund_policy.title %></strong>. All new purchases will follow this policy,
    and the "No refunds allowed" option is unavailable on your account for now.
  </p>
  <p>
    While this policy is enforced, it applies to your whole account and can't be changed in
    <%= link_to "Settings", settings_main_url %>. To request a different refund period of at
    least 7 days, reply to this email with the specific steps you've taken to reduce disputes,
    and we'll apply the change for you.
  </p>
  <p>
    Offering refunds directly is almost always cheaper than a chargeback, and it keeps your
    customers happier too. Once your dispute rate improves, we can restore full control over
    your refund policy — just reply to this email if you have questions.
  </p>
</div>
